King's Indian exchange, which isn't common to most players. White or Black should know how to play this line. Take me for example, I lost a point in a OTB chess tournament once, and I've only played against it once in a tournament, because I was dumbfounded when an opponent decided to play this line; I was not ready and didn't even know what the lines were!
